# Cloudflare DEPLOY credentials for this project.
# (NOT runtime vars -- those live in .dev.vars. This is only for `wrangler deploy`.)
#
# Setup:
#   1. cp .cloudflare.env.example .cloudflare.env      # the copy is gitignored
#   2. In the Cloudflare dashboard for the EMBODY account (id
#      6a37e9b97eb8cf7ac208714658168a8c) -> My Profile -> API Tokens ->
#      create a token with the "Edit Cloudflare Workers" template.
#   3. Paste it after the = below, in .cloudflare.env (not this example file).
#   4. ./deploy.sh
#
# This token must have access to the embody account; deploy.sh + the pinned
# account_id in wrangler.jsonc guarantee the deploy targets that account
# regardless of which account `wrangler login` is currently using.
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
